 the extraordinary, of poverty and beauty, of the experience of being one among many. Penned by one of its most prominent writers, Slow Trains Overhead evokes and commemorates human life in a great city.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aPOETRY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226290614423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226290614.jpg  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles